            "widgets_values": [
              "Extreme wide establishing telephoto shot (85–135mm look) of a solitary man walking to work along a city block at early morning. Long‑lens compression with shallow depth isolates him against storefronts while foreground poles and passing cars smear into soft bokeh. Lighting: natural dawn paired with glowing practical shop windows and lingering string lights, a gentle backlight edging his coat and soft bounce from pale walls; highlights halate realistically. Color grade: high‑contrast black‑and‑white with fine film grain, deep blacks and silvery midtones. Mood: quiet, introspective, restrained. The camera glides in a smooth lateral track that parallels his pace with occasional subtle dolly drift; rich parallax from fences, signposts, and pedestrians keeps space coherent. Wind lifts his collar, breath and street steam drift, paper skitters, and distant buses rumble—grounded, physical realism."
            ]
          }
